\noindent \textcolor{myblue}{\textbf{Q1 LLM scaling:}}
To examine whether LLM priors drive VKnowU, we perform a controlled LLaVA-style scaling study (Qwen3-4B→8B).
As shown in Table~\ref{tab:REBUTTAL_LLAVA}, scaling yields marginal gains on VKnowU but larger gains on other benchmarks. If VKnowU were reducible to language priors, gains would be uniform across tasks; instead, the observed disparity indicates some tasks are bottlenecked by visual grounding rather than LLM size. Thus, VKnowU cannot be explained by language priors alone, but evaluates visual knowledge as a \textbf{bridge} between perception and reasoning.这样可以吗

